      <body>
         <listPerson>
            <person xml:id="pers1341">
               <p>Son of Col. <persName>Martin Madan</persName>, MP of
                     <placeName>Hertingfordbury</placeName>, the younger <persName>Martin</persName>
                  prepared for a career in law. He was goaded into listening to <persName><ptr
                        target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName> preach, as a means of
                  improving his oratory style. But <persName>Madan</persName> was so moved by the
                  sermon that he joined the Methodist cause. With the aid of the <persName><ptr
                        target="/persons/pers0964.xml"/>Countess of Huntingdon</persName> he secured
                  ordination in <date when="1757">1757</date>, was appointed chaplain to Lock
                  Hospital in <placeName>London</placeName>, and became very friendly with many
                  Calvinistic evangelical clergy, especially <persName>David Jones</persName>,
                        <persName><ptr target="/persons/pers1771.xml"/>William Romaine</persName>,
                  and <persName><ptr target="/persons/pers2221.xml"/>George Whitefield</persName>.
                  In later years he gained notoriety for defending polygamy in <hi rend="italic"
                     >Thelyphthora</hi> (<date when="1780">1780</date>). See <hi rend="italic"
                     >DEB</hi>, 733; and <hi rend="italic">ODNB</hi>.</p>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
      </body>
   </text>
